{"article_id":"Y6IPxa6gTJb8zXwa","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"NSA leaker Edward Snowden was frantically trying to find a country","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"that would grant him asylum Tuesday ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"sending out a slew of requests to nearly 20 additional nations","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"as a short-lived bid","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"to take refuge in Russia","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"appeared to fizzle .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"Now , his best hope","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"for leaving the transit zone at the Moscow airport ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"where he is thought to have spent the past week ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"may be the president of Venezuela","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"-- who was in Moscow on Tuesday","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"meeting with Russian President Vladimir Putin .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Venezuela was among the 19 countries","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"that Snowden requested asylum with late Sunday ,","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"according to WikiLeaks .","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"The anti-secrecy group ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"which is aiding Snowden ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"revealed the scope of Snowden 's asylum requests Monday night .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"The group confirmed earlier reports","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"that Snowden sought to take refuge in Russia .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"But on Tuesday , Russian news agencies quoted President Vladimir Putin 's spokesman Dmitry Peskov","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"as saying","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"that Snowden withdrew his request","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"after learning about the terms","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"Moscow set out .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"Putin said on Monday","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"that Russia is ready to shelter Snowden","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"only if he stops leaking U.S. secrets","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"-- a condition","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"Snowden apparently was not prepared to meet .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"Other nations , though , were already indicating","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"they could not consider asylum","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"if Snowden was not on their soil .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"Attention turned Tuesday to Venezuela 's new president , Nicolas Maduro ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"who dodged the question","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"of whether he would take Snowden away with him .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"But Maduro ,","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"speaking to Russian reporters ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"also defended the former National Security Agency contractor","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"who released sensitive documents on U.S. intelligence-gathering operations .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"`` He did not kill anyone","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"and did not plant a bomb , ''","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Maduro said ,","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"the Interfax news agency reported .","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"`` What he did was tell a great truth in an effort","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"to prevent wars .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"He deserves protection under international and humanitarian law . ''","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"Putin on Monday was mum about the possibility","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"of another world leader whisking Snowden away .","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"But so far , Snowden is running into obstacle after obstacle","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"as he tries to negotiate a way out of the transit zone in the Moscow airport ,","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"without a valid U.S. passport or any country","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"that so far has agreed to take him .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"Several of the countries","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"he appealed to Sunday","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"he can not apply from abroad .","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"Officials in Germany , Norway , Austria , Poland , Finland , Switzerland and Spain all said","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"he must make his request on their soil .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"WikiLeaks said","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"requests have also been made to Bolivia , Brazil , China , Cuba , Ecuador , France , Iceland , India , Italy , Ireland , Netherlands , Nicaragua , Spain and Venezuela .","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"India 's External Affairs Ministry spokesman Syed Akbaruddin says","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"Delhi has carefully examined the asylum request","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"and decided to turn it down .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"Akbaruddin said Tuesday","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"that the government has `` concluded","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"that we see no reason","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"to accede to that request . ''","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"Amid the roadblocks , Snowden broke his weeklong silence on Monday ,","depth":4},{"id":69,"text":"defending his `` right","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"to seek asylum ''","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"while separately claiming","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"he remains `` free and able '' to publish sensitive information on U.S. surveillance .","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"In a statement","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"issued on the WikiLeaks website ,","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"Snowden attacked the Obama administration ,","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"saying ,","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"`` On Thursday , President Obama declared before the world","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"that he would not permit any diplomatic 'wheeling and dealing ' over my case .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"Yet now it is being reported","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"after promising not to do so ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"the President ordered his Vice President to pressure the leaders of nations","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"from which I have requested protection","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"to deny my asylum petitions . `` This kind of deception from a world leader is not justice ,","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"and neither is the extralegal penalty of exile . ''","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"He continued ,","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"`` Without any judicial order ,","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"the administration now seeks to stop me exercising a basic right .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"A right","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"that belongs to everybody .","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"The right","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"to seek asylum . ''","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"Separately , in a letter in Spanish","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"sent by Snowden to Ecuador President Rafael Correa","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"and obtained and translated by Britain 's Press Association ,","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"he declared ,","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"`` I remain free","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"and able to publish information","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"that serves the public interest .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"No matter how many more days my life contains ,","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"I remain dedicated to the fight for justice in this unequal world . ''","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"It was the first known statement from Snowden","depth":5},{"id":103,"text":"since he flew out of Hong Kong into Moscow more than a week ago .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":207,"left":136,"right":206,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":136,"left":109,"right":135,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":109,"left":106,"right":108,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":105,"right":2,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"left":107,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":107,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":135,"left":117,"right":134,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":114,"right":116,"relation":"elaboration","nuc